title: Print, "Plate in Vasses de la Maison Royalle de L'oo Nouvellement (Vessels of the Royal House of L'oo)", ca. 1700
medium: Etching and engraving on white laid paper
signed: Signed in plate, lower right: inventé et gravé par D. Marot.
inscribed: Inscribed in plate, lower left: auec Previlege des Etats Generaux.
creditline: Museum purchase from General Acquisitions Endowment Fund
description: Foot vessel decorated with garlands, foliage, and classical figures, and topped with a crown. At the center, a cartouche is decorated with an enthroned classical female figure wearing a crown, and surrounded by two putti and a lion.
